301
00:19:01,640 --> 00:19:03,840
So before coming to work here,

302
00:19:04,360 --> 00:19:09,040
I want you two to study all of the products we have made

303
00:19:09,840 --> 00:19:12,440
As there’s a risk involved here in this department.

304
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:14,240
We may give you a hard time.

305
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:19,520
But we take care of one another like brothers.

306
00:19:20,880 --> 00:19:21,840
I apologize for what I did earlier

307
00:19:22,040 --> 00:19:23,240
It was my carelessness.

308
00:19:25,880 --> 00:19:26,960
Please excuse me.

309
00:19:27,920 --> 00:19:28,720
See you again soon.

310
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:30,120
Cherry,

311
00:19:30,680 --> 00:19:32,120
have this fixed too.

312
00:19:35,080 --> 00:19:36,080
Well,

313
00:19:36,120 --> 00:19:38,120
I take you two to P’Durian

314
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:46,920
Want some?

315
00:19:47,960 --> 00:19:49,120
Thank you.

316
00:20:00,480 --> 00:20:01,960
Kids,

317
00:20:02,440 --> 00:20:03,320
what are you eating?

318
00:20:03,440 --> 00:20:04,640
It looks yum.

319
00:20:05,280 --> 00:20:06,600
Do you want some?

320
00:20:06,960 --> 00:20:08,200
No, I’m good.

321
00:20:08,640 --> 00:20:09,360
So?

322
00:20:09,560 --> 00:20:11,160
You have toured around the company?

323
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:13,360
How was it? Did you have a good time?

324
00:20:13,840 --> 00:20:14,840
It was very good.

325
00:20:16,160 --> 00:20:17,880
You can have a break now.

326
00:20:18,160 --> 00:20:20,040
But I want you to take these letters

327
00:20:20,240 --> 00:20:23,000
to the Procurement and the Production departments?

328
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:28,120
The Procurement Department, Ocean Electric Co., LTD

329
00:20:31,360 --> 00:20:32,360
Okay.

330
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:05,760
P’Arthit krap,

331
00:21:06,520 --> 00:21:07,720
I can explain.

332
00:21:09,880 --> 00:21:11,280
I’m working.

333
00:21:11,560 --> 00:21:13,560
I don’t feel like listening to anything at the moment.

334
00:21:14,160 --> 00:21:15,160
Kongpob,

335
00:21:15,600 --> 00:21:16,440
you are here to be an intern.

336
00:21:16,520 --> 00:21:18,520
Go back to your work

337
00:21:19,160 --> 00:21:20,680
P’Arthit, please listen to me.

338
00:21:21,160 --> 00:21:24,080
I couldn’t find the right time to tell you

339
00:21:24,520 --> 00:21:25,920
Don’t be mad at me.

340
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:29,520
I really want to do the internship here

341
00:21:30,280 --> 00:21:31,280
Well,

342
00:21:31,840 --> 00:21:34,280
since you started working here.

343
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:37,520
You told me a lot of things

344
00:21:38,880 --> 00:21:40,320
So I think

345
00:21:40,480 --> 00:21:42,040
if I do the internship here,

346
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:44,520
I will get more experiences than other companies

347
00:21:45,080 --> 00:21:45,920
Plus,

348
00:21:46,800 --> 00:21:49,280
I also get to see you working

349
00:21:49,680 --> 00:21:50,960
I can be near you

350
00:21:51,320 --> 00:21:52,560
and help you

351
00:21:52,840 --> 00:21:54,720
But you should have told me at least.

352
00:21:56,880 --> 00:21:59,560
Normally, we can talk about anything, right?

353
00:22:02,160 --> 00:22:03,200
I’m sorry.

354
00:22:05,240 --> 00:22:06,800
What about MCC?

355
00:22:08,840 --> 00:22:10,000
Forget it.

356
00:22:10,360 --> 00:22:12,040
You are here anyway.

357
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:14,640
Don’t forget to tell me again.

358
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:17,240
Okay, P’Arthit.

359
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:20,680
And what are you doing here?

360
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:24,200
P’Durian asked me to give this to P’Earth

361
00:22:25,520 --> 00:22:26,880
I’m going to give this to P’Earth later.

362
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:27,800
You can leave it with me.

363
00:22:32,040 --> 00:22:33,640
Go back to your work.

364
00:22:34,560 --> 00:22:36,120
Hold on, P’Arthit.

365
00:22:40,240 --> 00:22:41,600
Well…

366
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:44,120
Arthit,

367
00:22:44,440 --> 00:22:47,440
P’Danai is calling for you to give him the summary of our manufacturing tour.

368
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:08,840
Cherry,

369
00:23:09,040 --> 00:23:11,760
I finished fixing the fan that was broken down.

370
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:14,800
Oh.

371
00:23:16,040 --> 00:23:17,840
What are you doing here?

372
00:23:18,920 --> 00:23:22,560
Oh, I’m looking at what you are doing

373
00:23:24,920 --> 00:23:28,400
I mean what you are doing here?

374
00:23:29,680 --> 00:23:33,400
I have a letter for you from P’Durian

375
00:23:33,640 --> 00:23:36,240
My hands are dirty.

376
00:23:36,680 --> 00:23:38,800
Can you put it on my desk for me?

377
00:23:41,440 --> 00:23:42,680
Uh…

378
00:23:45,280 --> 00:23:47,240
where is your desk?

379
00:23:47,320 --> 00:23:49,000
The one with a coffee mug.

380
00:24:01,640 --> 00:24:06,680
And can you tell me what you are doing?

381
00:24:10,880 --> 00:24:13,280
I’m fixing the fan you broke.

382
00:24:13,360 --> 00:24:14,760
Don’t be kidding.

383
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:16,000
It wasn’t me.

384
00:24:16,320 --> 00:24:17,720
The fan exploded by itself.

385
00:24:18,320 --> 00:24:19,560
I knew.

386
00:24:19,840 --> 00:24:20,840
When I sent it to fix,

387
00:24:21,040 --> 00:24:24,280
they say the wires got fused together by mistake.

388
00:24:24,560 --> 00:24:26,960
So it caused the short circuit and banged.

389
00:24:28,160 --> 00:24:31,880
Do you have to check the motor and the electrical panel again?

390
00:24:32,240 --> 00:24:34,680
I heard a weird sound coming out of it.

391
00:24:35,080 --> 00:24:37,680
Maybe, something is wrong with the sound box.

392
00:24:38,160 --> 00:24:39,640
You may want to check those again.

393
00:24:40,040 --> 00:24:41,560
I did check them all.

394
00:24:42,160 --> 00:24:44,360
What’s your name again?

395
00:24:46,800 --> 00:24:48,160
My name?

396
00:24:48,440 --> 00:24:50,520
Yes, what’s your name?

397
00:24:51,120 --> 00:24:53,480
My name is Weerawat.

398
00:24:54,800 --> 00:24:56,320
You don’t have a nickname?

399
00:24:56,600 --> 00:24:58,480
You already knew my nickname.

400
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:02,440
Your nickname is also Weerawat?

401
00:25:04,720 --> 00:25:07,840
No, my nickname is Nai.

402
00:25:08,200 --> 00:25:10,520
I heard you call me “Nai” many times

403
00:25:10,680 --> 00:25:12,000
so I thought you knew. (Note: Nai also means “You”)

404
00:25:12,360 --> 00:25:13,200
I see.

405
00:25:13,320 --> 00:25:14,480
Nai.

406
00:25:16,680 --> 00:25:17,960
P’Yong,

407
00:25:18,080 --> 00:25:19,760
the fan is finished, right?

408
00:25:19,840 --> 00:25:21,760
I can put it back.

409
00:25:22,760 --> 00:25:25,320
Hi, Nong Nai.

410
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:27,240
You come all the way to here.

411
00:25:27,320 --> 00:25:28,160
What can I do for you?

412
00:25:28,280 --> 00:25:29,040
Could it be that

413
00:25:29,240 --> 00:25:31,320
you are missing me?

414
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:35,440
I’m here to drop a letter.

415
00:25:36,320 --> 00:25:37,360
Seriously,

416
00:25:37,440 --> 00:25:39,280
you can just say something I want to hear.

417
00:25:40,160 --> 00:25:41,200
Well,

418
00:25:41,720 --> 00:25:45,000
would you mind put this fan to where it was?

419
00:25:45,840 --> 00:25:47,840
You are done, right?

420
00:25:48,520 --> 00:25:49,960
Okay, boss.

421
00:25:51,400 --> 00:25:52,840
It’s heavy.

422
00:25:52,880 --> 00:25:55,080
You can help me carry the cord

423
00:25:55,240 --> 00:25:56,000
Okay.

424
00:25:56,320 --> 00:25:58,080
We’re going, P’Yong.

425
00:26:39,440 --> 00:26:40,480
Hello, yes.

426
00:26:42,800 --> 00:26:44,840
I have arrived

427
00:26:45,320 --> 00:26:48,760
I’m waiting to get the interview

428
00:26:57,520 --> 00:26:58,880
Thank you.

429
00:27:20,480 --> 00:27:21,760
I have got off work.

430
00:27:22,080 --> 00:27:23,360
Have you finished your work?

431
00:27:23,800 --> 00:27:25,520
Would you like to go back together?

432
00:27:25,720 --> 00:27:26,880
I have a meeting.

433
00:27:27,040 --> 00:27:28,600
I probably get off work late

434
00:27:28,760 --> 00:27:30,400
You can go back without me.

435
00:27:31,160 --> 00:27:32,240
Kong.

436
00:27:32,560 --> 00:27:33,680
Hey, Nai.

437
00:27:34,200 --> 00:27:35,520
You just got off work?

438
00:27:35,720 --> 00:27:37,200
Want to go back together?

439
00:27:37,480 --> 00:27:38,080
Um.

440
00:27:38,280 --> 00:27:40,320
How do you go home?

441
00:27:40,640 --> 00:27:42,120
With this motorcycle.

442
00:27:42,400 --> 00:27:42,880
Where do you stay?

443
00:27:42,960 --> 00:27:43,520
I can give you a ride

444
00:27:44,720 --> 00:27:46,600
You can drop me at the main street

445
00:27:46,840 --> 00:27:47,640
I can go home by bus.

446
00:27:47,720 --> 00:27:48,720
It’s quite far from here.

447
00:27:49,240 --> 00:27:49,720
Okay.

448
00:27:56,560 --> 00:27:57,560
Thanks.

449
00:28:01,360 --> 00:28:02,600
Hey, Day. Day.

450
00:28:02,960 --> 00:28:04,120
Well…

451
00:28:04,240 --> 00:28:05,400
What are you doing?

452
00:28:05,600 --> 00:28:07,080
Let go of me.

453
00:28:07,520 --> 00:28:10,160
You have to come with me no matter what

454
00:28:10,880 --> 00:28:12,360
Hey, what’s wrong with you?

455
00:28:12,560 --> 00:28:13,640
Day, wait.

456
00:28:13,800 --> 00:28:14,880
Hey,

457
00:28:15,520 --> 00:28:17,200
if you don’t let go of me.

458
00:28:17,400 --> 00:28:18,720
I’ll file a report the police

459
00:28:18,880 --> 00:28:20,280
on the charge of forcing juniors to attend the activities without their consent.

460
00:28:20,680 --> 00:28:22,240
You can get jailed up to 3 years, you know?

461
00:28:22,400 --> 00:28:23,480
I don’t mind

462
00:28:23,600 --> 00:28:25,800
The initiation activities have been long over since the beach day.

463
00:28:25,800 --> 00:28:28,280
Today, I want to take you to eat.

464
00:28:28,480 --> 00:28:29,040
Come on.

465
00:28:29,160 --> 00:28:30,000
Hey,

466
00:28:30,480 --> 00:28:31,920
Eat what? I don’t want to go.

467
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:33,160
Come on.

468
00:28:33,240 --> 00:28:34,000
Come with me.

469
00:28:34,280 --> 00:28:35,440
This is kidnapping.

470
00:28:35,560 --> 00:28:37,520
We will just eat.

471
00:28:39,120 --> 00:28:40,160
Be quiet.

472
00:28:40,320 --> 00:28:41,240
Hey.

473
00:28:42,720 --> 00:28:45,240
To a pub called Fin Jung at Jindarat alley

474
00:28:45,720 --> 00:28:47,720
You are dripping the drink in his car.

475
00:28:47,840 --> 00:28:49,080
Where are we going?

476
00:28:49,600 --> 00:28:51,320
You can go now.

477
00:28:57,480 --> 00:28:58,480
Tew.

478
00:28:59,280 --> 00:29:00,720
Hi, Day.

479
00:29:02,200 --> 00:29:03,200
P’Yod.

480
00:29:03,400 --> 00:29:04,600
Sawasdee krap, P’Yod.

481
00:29:04,800 --> 00:29:06,800
You don’t have to Wai me.

482
00:29:08,080 --> 00:29:10,040
I asked you to bring our line junior

483
00:29:10,200 --> 00:29:11,720
don’t tell me he is that junior.

484
00:29:12,840 --> 00:29:13,840
Yes.

485
00:29:15,040 --> 00:29:17,040
So you are my line junior?

486
00:29:17,480 --> 00:29:19,160
What a small world.

487
00:29:21,320 --> 00:29:22,480
What’s line junior?

488
00:29:22,680 --> 00:29:24,240
The line of student ID 0058.

489
00:29:24,520 --> 00:29:27,040
I call you guys to have a feast within our junior-senior in this student ID’s line.

490
00:29:27,600 --> 00:29:31,400
So you two know each other?

491
00:29:31,440 --> 00:29:31,880
Yes,

492
00:29:32,080 --> 00:29:34,320
I’m also his senior in the school.

493
00:29:34,800 --> 00:29:37,280
We were in the same club, actually.

494
00:29:37,480 --> 00:29:39,480
You transferred to here and started again as a first year.

495
00:29:39,760 --> 00:29:41,320
You were not okay with the old uni?

496
00:29:41,960 --> 00:29:42,800
Yes,

497
00:29:43,040 --> 00:29:44,480
I had some problem studying there.

498
00:29:44,600 --> 00:29:46,200
So I transferred to here

499
00:29:47,080 --> 00:29:49,480
Why you didn’t join us during the initiation ceremony

500
00:29:49,880 --> 00:29:51,960
I was busy.

501
00:29:53,120 --> 00:29:54,640
You were always busy.

502
00:29:54,760 --> 00:29:58,160
I invited him so many times and he refused to join

503
00:30:07,080 --> 00:30:07,560
How are you doing?

504
00:30:07,600 --> 00:30:08,800
Long time no see.

505
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:11,080
I haven’t seen you after you graduated

506
00:30:11,280 --> 00:30:12,120
What?

507
00:30:12,280 --> 00:30:12,760
I have already graduated.

508
00:30:12,840 --> 00:30:13,960
Why do you still expect to see me there?

509
00:30:14,040 --> 00:30:16,160
I have completed my degree. I’m not going back there

510
00:30:16,520 --> 00:30:18,240
You can just come pay us a visit.

511
00:30:18,400 --> 00:30:20,080
All right, I will go if there are a lot of female students

512
00:30:20,200 --> 00:30:22,400
I go to where female students are.

513
00:30:22,960 --> 00:30:23,520
All right. Make yourself at home

514
00:30:23,640 --> 00:30:24,720
Thank you so much.

515
00:30:25,920 --> 00:30:27,800
By the way, P’Yod.

516
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:30,800
In the past,

517
00:30:31,160 --> 00:30:32,560
you didn’t seem to appreciate the initiation process

518
00:30:32,800 --> 00:30:35,800
Why did you join it here?

519
00:30:36,280 --> 00:30:37,800
I still don’t like it

520
00:30:38,120 --> 00:30:43,040
But the initiation allows us to know other people more

521
00:30:43,200 --> 00:30:45,760
We still have to live with others.

522
00:30:46,080 --> 00:30:47,520
We have to belong in the society

523
00:30:47,680 --> 00:30:49,040
That’s right

524
00:30:49,960 --> 00:30:53,280
Well, let me officially open the party of our student ID’s line

525
00:30:53,600 --> 00:30:54,720
Come on

526
00:30:55,600 --> 00:30:57,040
Officially?

527
00:30:57,680 --> 00:31:01,640
Are you saying that these are all we have in this line?

528
00:31:01,760 --> 00:31:02,920
Yeah.

529
00:31:02,960 --> 00:31:04,840
The junior from last year has already transferred to another uni

530
00:31:04,960 --> 00:31:07,160
My senior is furthering study somewhere else.

531
00:31:07,280 --> 00:31:08,920
So these are all we have

532
00:31:08,960 --> 00:31:10,440
That’s right.

533
00:31:10,600 --> 00:31:13,240
It’s not about the number of people

534
00:31:13,440 --> 00:31:15,240
It’s the way we communicate,

535
00:31:15,400 --> 00:31:16,400
understand

536
00:31:16,680 --> 00:31:18,600
and help one another.

537
00:31:19,360 --> 00:31:20,360
Come on.

538
00:31:20,760 --> 00:31:21,920
Hey!

539
00:31:30,960 --> 00:31:31,840
So, Tew.

540
00:31:32,040 --> 00:31:34,240
You finally have a line junior.

541
00:31:35,640 --> 00:31:36,160
Yes.

542
00:31:37,080 --> 00:31:38,400
It’s amazing

543
00:31:50,440 --> 00:31:51,640
P’Earth,

544
00:31:52,360 --> 00:31:54,640
P’John and Som-O invite me to have dinner altogether.

545
00:31:54,760 --> 00:31:56,080
Would you like to join us?

546
00:31:57,680 --> 00:31:59,440
Well, I’m a bit tired today

547
00:31:59,560 --> 00:32:01,120
I should go home

548
00:32:03,440 --> 00:32:04,440
Arthit,

549
00:32:04,800 --> 00:32:06,760
are you going to eat with P’John?

550
00:32:07,720 --> 00:32:09,600
I have to excuse myself today.

551
00:32:09,760 --> 00:32:11,760
It’s raining. I should go home.

552
00:32:11,920 --> 00:32:13,400
I can give you a lift.

553
00:32:14,240 --> 00:32:15,320
It’s okay. I don’t want to impose on you.

554
00:32:15,520 --> 00:32:16,600
Don’t worry.

555
00:32:16,720 --> 00:32:19,440
This kind of rain is not going to stop easily

556
00:32:22,560 --> 00:32:24,760
Well, see you tomorrow, Tod.

557
00:32:25,240 --> 00:32:27,560
P’Som-O, goodbye.

558
00:32:28,280 --> 00:32:29,320
Tod.

559
00:32:29,760 --> 00:32:30,440
Tod.

560
00:32:30,680 --> 00:32:31,040
Yes?

561
00:32:31,160 --> 00:32:33,600
Wait a moment, P’John is bringing his car to here.

562
00:32:33,920 --> 00:32:34,760
Okay.

563
00:32:39,040 --> 00:32:40,120
it's raining cats and dogs.

564
00:32:46,320 --> 00:32:48,000
Listen, Day.

565
00:32:49,120 --> 00:32:50,320
Well…

566
00:32:51,800 --> 00:32:52,960
I want to point out to you that

